Package: binaryRL
Type: Package
Title: Reinforcement Learning tools for Two-Alternative Forced Choice tasks
Version: 0.5.8
Author: yuki <hmz1969a@gmail.com>
Maintainer: yuki <hmz1969a@gmail.com>
Description: This package provides tools for fitting reinforcement learning 
  models to Two-Alternative Forced Choice (TAFC) decision-making tasks. 
  Users first construct a reinforcement learning model using the `run_m` 
  function and then optimize its free parameters with `fit_p`. Additionally, 
  the package includes `simulate_l` and `recovery_d` functions for parameter 
  recovery and model recovery, enabling users to assess model performance.
